						               													<description>A master potter is seeking to train an apprentice to take over their studio! You must prove yourself worthy of the position by showing your dedication for learning the craft. Manage your time and resources effectively, and gain as much experience behind the Potter's Wheel as you can before the master potter must pick their disciple.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Potter's Apprentice is a strategic Euro game of hand and resource management. The game's circular board surrounds a rotating &amp;quot;Potter's Wheel,&amp;quot; which players will interact with as they move their apprentice around the board. The core gameplay consists of the players utilizing their Action Cards in 1 of 2 ways:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Playing on the main board to take a location's various actions or&amp;#10;- Adding to their player board to permanently increase 1 of their skills&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As the players collect different clays, tools and water, they will make (&amp;quot;throw&amp;quot;) pottery! They may need assistance from the Master Potter who moves around the board too. However, with each piece made the player will gain Experience and gradually unlock the ability to work on more pieces without supervision.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory Points will be earned for completed assignments, pottery, and various other scoring objectives acquired throughout the game. The player with the most VP at the end of the game is chosen as the potter's apprentice!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
